<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,640,1063]" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">
<bibRefCitation author="Gorodkov, K. B." box="[151,347,641,668]" pageId="1" pageNumber="472" pagination="11 - 41" refId="ref6607" refString="Gorodkov, K. B. (1986) Family Scathophagidae. In: Soos, A. &amp; Papp, L. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Diptera. Vol. 11. Akademiai Kiado, Budapest, pp. 11 - 41." type="book chapter" year="1986">Gorodkov (1986)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Jong, H. D." box="[404,540,641,667]" pageId="1" pageNumber="472" pagination="431 - 445" refId="ref6721" refString="Jong, H. D. (2000) Family Scathophagidae. In: Papp, L. &amp; Darvas, B. L. (Eds.), Contributions to a Manual of Palaearctic Diptera. Appendix. Science Herald, Budapest, pp. 431 - 445." type="book chapter" year="2000">Jong (2000)</bibRefCitation>
recognized three subgenera (
<taxonomicName authority="Fallen, 1810" authorityName="Fallen" authorityYear="1810" box="[873,1136,641,667]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Cordilura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="472" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[873,984,641,667]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">Cordilura</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fallen, C. F." box="[992,1136,641,667]" pageId="1" pageNumber="472" refId="ref6582" refString="Fallen, C. F. (1810) Specimen entomologicum novam Diptera disponendi methodum exhibens. Litteris Berlingianis, Lundae, 26 pp." type="book" year="1810">Fallén, 1810</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[1148,1281,641,667]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">Cordilurina</emphasis>
James, 1955; and 
<taxonomicName authority="Becker, 1894" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1894" box="[199,498,677,703]" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Scoliaphleps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="472" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,342,677,703]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">Scoliaphleps</emphasis>
Becker, 1894
</taxonomicName>
) in the Palaearctic 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fallen" authorityYear="1810" box="[713,824,677,703]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Cordilura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="472" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[713,824,677,703]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">Cordilura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but these were not accepted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sifner, F." box="[1190,1340,676,703]" pageId="1" pageNumber="472" pagination="111 - 196" refId="ref7500" refString="Sifner, F. (2008) A catalogue of the Scathophagidae (Diptera) of the Palaearctic region, with notes on their taxonomy and faunistics. Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 48, 111 - 196." type="journal article" year="2008">Šifner (2008)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Ozerov, A. L. &amp; Krivosheina, M. G." pageId="1" pageNumber="472" pagination="203 - 222" refId="ref7255" refString="Ozerov, A. L. &amp; Krivosheina, M. G. (2014) To the fauna of dung flies (Diptera: Scathophagidae) of Russian Far East. Russian Entomological Journal, 23, 203 - 222. https: // doi. org / 10.15298 / rusentj. 23.3.07" type="journal article" year="2014">Ozerov &amp; Krivosheina (2014)</bibRefCitation>
. In the present paper I follow 
<bibRefCitation author="Sifner, F." box="[782,931,712,739]" pageId="1" pageNumber="472" pagination="111 - 196" refId="ref7500" refString="Sifner, F. (2008) A catalogue of the Scathophagidae (Diptera) of the Palaearctic region, with notes on their taxonomy and faunistics. Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 48, 111 - 196." type="journal article" year="2008">Šifner (2008)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Ozerov, A. L. &amp; Krivosheina, M. G." box="[982,1318,713,739]" pageId="1" pageNumber="472" pagination="203 - 222" refId="ref7255" refString="Ozerov, A. L. &amp; Krivosheina, M. G. (2014) To the fauna of dung flies (Diptera: Scathophagidae) of Russian Far East. Russian Entomological Journal, 23, 203 - 222. https: // doi. org / 10.15298 / rusentj. 23.3.07" type="journal article" year="2014">Ozerov &amp; Krivosheina (2014)</bibRefCitation>
, therefore, this genus is defined by the following combination of characteristics.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="472" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,640,1063]" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,784,811]" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Head yellow to black; 3–4 
<emphasis box="[646,665,785,811]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">fr</emphasis>
, 2–3 
<emphasis box="[732,757,786,811]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">or</emphasis>
(proclinate, lateroclinate, lateroreclinate) (
<figureCitation box="[1246,1332,785,812]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–16" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1707,1732]" captionTargetBox="[207,1355,1162,1677]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[207,1381,1156,1681]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 15–16. Cordilura nubecula Sasakawa, specimen from Hokkaido. 15, female adult, left lateral view. 16, female head, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3701087" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3701087/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
); 1 
<emphasis box="[1379,1405,786,811]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">oc</emphasis>
, 1 
<emphasis box="[151,191,822,847]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">poc</emphasis>
, 1 
<emphasis box="[228,261,822,847]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">vte</emphasis>
, 1 
<emphasis box="[297,325,822,847]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">vti</emphasis>
; postpedicel 2–3 times as long as wide (
<figureCitation box="[782,855,821,847]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1930,1955]" captionTargetBox="[358,1229,185,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[358,1229,181,1904]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–9. Cordilura cuspidata Sasakawa, specimen from Hokkaido. 5, male adult, left lateral vew; 6, male postpedicel and pedicel, left lateral view; 7, male palpus, left lateral view; 8, male terminalia, left lateral view; 9, male terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3701081" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3701081/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">Figs 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[868,899,821,847]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1963,1988]" captionTargetBox="[256,1331,633,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[256,1331,633,1937]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Cordilura remmi Elberg, specimen from Hokkaido. 17, male adult, lateral view; 18, postpedicel and pedicel, left lateral view; 19, male terminalia, lateral view; 20, male terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3701089" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3701089/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">18</figureCitation>
); arista plumose or short-haired; vibrissal angle with 1 vibrissae and 1 subvibrissa; palpus with 1 strong subapical seta as long as or longer than palpus (
<figureCitation box="[1351,1421,857,883]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1930,1955]" captionTargetBox="[358,1229,185,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[358,1229,181,1904]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–9. Cordilura cuspidata Sasakawa, specimen from Hokkaido. 5, male adult, left lateral vew; 6, male postpedicel and pedicel, left lateral view; 7, male palpus, left lateral view; 8, male terminalia, left lateral view; 9, male terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3701081" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3701081/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); proepisternum covered by hairs at middle or on anterior part; 2 
<emphasis box="[879,932,894,919]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">pprn</emphasis>
, 2 
<emphasis box="[970,1006,893,919]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">npl</emphasis>
; 1 
<emphasis box="[1044,1138,893,919]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">prest ial</emphasis>
; 2+3 
<emphasis box="[1206,1232,893,919]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">dc</emphasis>
, 2 
<emphasis box="[1270,1295,894,919]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">sa</emphasis>
, 2 
<emphasis box="[1333,1361,894,919]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">pa</emphasis>
, 1 
<emphasis box="[1399,1436,893,919]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">dsc</emphasis>
(strong), 1 
<emphasis box="[273,324,930,955]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">apsc</emphasis>
(generally small), 1–2 
<emphasis box="[580,649,930,955]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">prepst</emphasis>
, 1 
<emphasis box="[681,752,930,955]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">prepm</emphasis>
; 1–5 
<emphasis box="[813,886,930,955]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">anepst</emphasis>
, 1 
<emphasis box="[919,977,929,955]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">kepst</emphasis>
; vein A 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1063,1071,946,960]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">1</subScript>
+CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1140,1148,946,960]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">2</subScript>
extending to wing margin or abruptly ending well before wing margin; fore femur and tibia without ventral row of long spinous setae; male sternite V prominently bilobate posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[647,716,1001,1027]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1485,1510]" captionTargetBox="[317,1271,179,1428]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[317,1271,179,1458]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Cordilura albipes (Fallén), specimen from Kyushu. 1, male adult, dorsal view; 2, male sternite V; 3, male terminalia, left lateral view; 4, male terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3701079" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3701079/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
); male surstylus slender or stout, or often bifurcate into anterior and posterior lobes apically (
<figureCitation box="[475,576,1037,1063]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1485,1510]" captionTargetBox="[317,1271,179,1428]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[317,1271,179,1458]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Cordilura albipes (Fallén), specimen from Kyushu. 1, male adult, dorsal view; 2, male sternite V; 3, male terminalia, left lateral view; 4, male terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3701079" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3701079/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="472">Figs 3, 4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
